name: IdentityClientWebApp
description: This is a web application for testing IdentityServer from client side. Our microservices is Restful APIs. So this web application uses HttpClients to communicate with services. To access those services, web app must be authenticated. IdentityServer generates a jwt token to provide policy/claim/role based authentication. Web app achieves this token via IdentityServer's HttpClient and stores access_token in memory cache. If token expires, then tries to retrieve a new token using refresh_token. I am simulating all that with using this web application in client side.

name: CatalogueWebApp
description: This is the web version of a JEE web application that allows you to manage products classified by categories:  - The Backend part is based on two micro-services:       - A micro-service based on Spring IOC, Spring Data, Spring Data Rest, Spring Security JPA, Hibernate that allows you to manage products and categories. In this microservice, products and categories are stored in a NoSQL MongoDB database.       - An authentication micro-service that takes care of the security part based on Spring Security and Json Web Token (JWT). In this microservice, users and roles are stored in a SQL database (H2 or MySQL). MySQL in this case.  - The Frontend part is based on Angular
